Authentication

Bearer Authentication

Authorization with Bearer token in GraphQL

Add "Authorization": "Bearer <token> in the header (replace <token> with the access token)

This token will be used to authenticate the user.

type
apiKey
name
Bearer Authentication
in
header

Auth Section

Authentication and authorization queries and mutations such as login, register, logout, and so on.

Auth Section

Verify Forgot Password

Matches the forgot password token and verifies them with the token saved in the database. After successful verification of the forgot password token, the new password is saved to the database.

forgotPasswordToken:
string

(no description)

options:
PasswordInput

(no description)

Example

Request Content-Types: application/json
Query
mutation verifyForgotPassword($forgotPasswordToken: String!, $options: PasswordInput!){
  verifyForgotPassword(forgotPasswordToken: $forgotPasswordToken, options: $options)
}
Variables
{
  "forgotPasswordToken": "string",
  "options": {
    "password": "string"
  }
}
Try it now
200 OK

Successful operation

type
boolean
Response Content-Types: application/json
Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  "data": {
    "verifyForgotPassword": "boolean"
  }
}
